    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the pork has 15 min left, add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
