    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and once hot, add the<strong> onion wedges</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Once slightly softened, add the<strong> tomato wedges </strong>with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> sugar </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until softened but not completely broken down – this is your <strong>hogao-style tomato</strong></p>",
